<emphasis id="51F7EAE1FFF3FFFF1ED138B8FF5AFE37" bold="true" box="[189,248,416,442]" pageId="39" pageNumber="65">Note</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="633C36F3FFF3FFFF1ED138D3FE37FDA6" blockId="39.[187,1399,416,555]" pageId="39" pageNumber="65">
We propose 
<taxonomicName id="A4834D70FFF3FFFF1F2638D3FDE9FE68" authorityName="Keyserling" authorityYear="1880" box="[330,587,459,485]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Stephanopis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="39" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="furcillata">
<emphasis id="51F7EAE1FFF3FFFF1F2638D3FDE9FE68" box="[330,587,459,485]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="65">Stephanopis furcillata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as senior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="A4834D70FFF3FFFF1D2038D3FAD0FE68" authority="(Mello-Leitao, 1944)" baseAuthorityName="Mello-Leitao" baseAuthorityYear="1944" box="[844,1394,459,485]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Sidymella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="39" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="multispinulosa">
<emphasis id="51F7EAE1FFF3FFFF1D2038D3FBD0FE68" box="[844,1138,459,485]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="65">Sidymella multispinulosa</emphasis>
(Mello-Leitão, 1944)
</taxonomicName>
, based on the distinct opisthosoma presenting a long pair of projections with a terminal tubercle at their tips (
<figureCitation id="FBB82A76FFF3FFFF1E943B09FE2AFDA6" box="[248,392,529,555]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="37.[189,232,1921,1947]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,711,1881]" captionTargetId="figure-121@37.[189,1398,711,1881]" captionText="Fig. 24. A–B. Holotype of Stephanopis borgmeyeri Mello-Leitão, 1929. Holotype (MNRJ 917). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Front. C–D. Stephanopis furcillata Keyserling, 1880. Holotype (ZMHB 2406). C. Habitus, dorsal view. D. Front." pageId="39" pageNumber="65">Fig. 24C–D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
